Neuroscience.structures.Organ¶

class Neuroscience.structures.Organ.Organ[source]¶

Bases: object

A class representing an organ in a neural network model, consisting of multiple neurons and managing their interactions.

The Organ class serves as a container for neurons, managing their connections, updating the adjacency matrix, and simulating the neural activity. It can be used to represent more complex structures within a neural network.

name¶

The name of the organ. If not overridden, defaults to “Your class does not implement name attribute (it should)”.

Type

str

brain¶

A list of neurons that make up the organ.

Type

list of Abstract_Neuron

input_neurons¶

A list of input neurons for the organ.

Type

list of Abstract_Neuron

output_neurons¶

A list of output neurons for the organ.

Type

list of Abstract_Neuron

network¶

A list representing the network connections within the organ.

Type

list

adjacency¶

An adjacency matrix representing the connections between neurons in the organ.

Type

AdjacencyMatrix

add_to_brain(neuron)[source]¶

Adds a neuron to the organ’s brain.

Parameters

neuron (Abstract_Neuron) – The neuron to be added to the brain list.

connect(index, neuron)[source]¶

Connects a neuron at a specified index in the brain to another neuron.

Parameters

  • index (int) – The index of the neuron in the brain list.

  • neuron (Abstract_Neuron) – The neuron to connect with.

get_voltage()[source]¶

Gets the voltage of the organ (currently a placeholder function).

Returns

A string indicating that this is the organ voltage.

Return type

str

print_network(name)[source]¶

Prints the network structure of the organ using the adjacency matrix.

Parameters

name (str) – The name for the graph or network being printed.

replace(index, neuron)[source]¶

Replaces a neuron at a specified index in the brain with another neuron.

Parameters

  • index (int) – The index of the neuron to be replaced.

  • neuron (Abstract_Neuron) – The new neuron to replace the old one.

simulate(k, V)[source]¶

Simulates the neural activity within the organ for a single time step.

Parameters

  • k (int) – The current time step in the simulation.

  • V (numpy.ndarray) – A matrix to store the membrane potentials of the neurons over time.

tune(index, weights)[source]¶

Tunes the weights of a specific neuron in the organ.

Parameters

  • index (int) – The index of the neuron in the brain list.

  • weights (list of float) – The new weights to be set for the neuron.

update_adjacency_matrix()[source]¶

Updates the adjacency matrix to reflect the current connections between neurons in the organ.

This is a costly function with a time complexity of O(n^2), where n is the number of neurons.
